main event: Mrs. ___ captured film footage of a disc-like phenomenon while taking pictures of contrails on June 7, 1960.
interesting points: The film shows a bright object that created a loud sonic boom heard by many in Sault Ste. Marie area.,The object was not visible to Mrs. ___ until after film processing.,Three 24"x34" negatives are included in the case.,The image processed from the film appeared to show a rectangular shape that became circular.,Contrails were noted in the sky, suggesting high-flying aircraft presence at the same time.
witness description: Mrs. ___ captured the event using a standard Brownie Kodak camera.
